## 

## PROGRAM OVERVIEW

+-----------+----------------------------------------------------------+
| **        | **Description**                                          |
| Section** |                                                          |
+===========+==========================================================+
| **PROBLEM | The Customer Success organization faces operational      |
| OR        | friction due to manual, labor-intensive workflows that   |
| ISSUE**   | scale linearly with headcount. Analysis indicates that   |
|           | CSMs allocate **30-40% of their weekly capacity** to     |
|           | non-strategic administrative tasks, including manual     |
|           | data aggregation from Salesforce, client call            |
|           | summarization, and routine correspondence drafting.      |
|           | Additionally, the fragmentation of adoption data across  |
|           | disparate systems (Salesforce, local files) impedes      |
|           | real-time visibility. Leadership forums frequently       |
|           | expend valuable time reconciling data accuracy rather    |
|           | than executing strategic decisions, due to the absence   |
|           | of a unified \"Golden Source\" for customer health       |
|           | metrics.                                                 |
+-----------+----------------------------------------------------------+
| **PURPOSE | To operationalize Artificial Intelligence across the     |
| OF        | Customer Success value chain, transitioning the          |
| PROGRAM** | organization from a service-based model to a             |
|           | technology-enabled engagement model. This program        |
|           | consolidates isolated pilot initiatives into a unified   |
|           | **\"Process Management System.\"** The strategic         |
|           | objective is to drive **high-velocity innovation** by    |
|           | unifying \"Migration\" (Technical Debt Retirement) and   |
|           | \"Adoption\" (Value Realization) activities under a      |
|           | single, rigorous governance framework, ensuring          |
|           | alignment with operational efficiency and commercial     |
|           | growth targets.                                          |
+-----------+----------------------------------------------------------+
| *         | Automating administrative workflows and standardizing    |
| *BUSINESS | the adoption process will unlock significant CSM         |
| CASE**    | capacity (Operational Efficiency), enabling a shift in   |
|           | focus toward high-value advisory work that drives Net    |
|           | Revenue Retention (NRR). Concurrently, equipping the     |
|           | pre-sales team with live, AI-driven prototyping tools    |
|           | will accelerate sales cycles (Commercial Value). This    |
|           | program strategically repositions Gen AI from a          |
|           | back-office efficiency lever to a **front-office revenue |
|           | accelerator**, differentiating our service offering in   |
|           | the market.                                              |
+-----------+----------------------------------------------------------+
| **PROGRAM | 1\. **Operational Efficiency:** Achieve a measurable     |
| GOALS**   | reduction in \"time-to-report\" for CSMs and reduce      |
|           | weekly stand-up duration by \>50% through management by  |
|           | exception.                                               |
|           |                                                          |
|           | 2\. **Data Integrity:** Achieve \>95% Data Completeness  |
|           | in the new system (eliminating undefined status fields)  |
|           | to enable accurate forecasting.                          |
|           |                                                          |
|           | 3\. **Commercial Impact:** Demonstrate a measurable      |
|           | \"Pipeline Conversion Lift\" for deals utilizing         |
|           | Cursor-based live demos versus standard static           |
|           | presentations.                                           |
|           |                                                          |
|           | 4\. **Support Deflection:** Deflect a significant        |
|           | percentage of Tier 1 support tickets via IRP Navigator   |
|           | L1 automation, optimizing support costs.                 |
|           |                                                          |
|           | 5\. **Upskilling:** Achieve a high \"Competency          |
|           | Conversion Rate,\" defined as the percentage of staff    |
|           | who deploy a working agent or automation within 30 days  |
|           | of training.                                             |
+-----------+----------------------------------------------------------+

