## PROJECT 1: TRAINING & ENABLEMENT (UPSKILLING)

+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Field**             | **Details**                                  |
+=======================+==============================================+
| **Project Lead**      | Training Lead (TBD) / Richard Dosoo          |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic Context** | To scale innovation effectively, we must     |
|                       | democratize technical capability beyond a    |
|                       | centralized team. This project transitions   |
|                       | the workforce from passive \"AI Awareness\"  |
|                       | to active \"AI Competency,\" fostering a     |
|                       | culture where functional leads are empowered |
|                       | to resolve efficiency challenges             |
|                       | independently.                               |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**             | \- **Microsoft Copilot & Moody's Copilot     |
|                       | Platform:** Integration into daily workflows |
|                       | (e.g., meeting summarization, content        |
|                       | generation) to drive productivity gains.     |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Copilot Studio Lite:** Training a       |
|                       | designated group of \"Citizen Developers\"   |
|                       | within CS to build custom \"Smart Agents\"   |
|                       | for specific team use cases.                 |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Cursor for Non-Engineers:** Enabling    |
|                       | functional leads to utilize code generation  |
|                       | tools for prototyping and understanding      |
|                       | technical possibilities.                     |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Target Metrics**    | **Competency Conversion Rate:** Success is   |
|                       | defined as the percentage of attendees who   |
|                       | deploy a working agent or automation within  |
|                       | 30 days of training, ensuring practical      |
|                       | application.                                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits &          | **Customer:** Customer Success Team (CSMs,   |
| Customers**           | Managers, Directors).                        |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Benefit:** A digitally fluent workforce    |
|                       | capable of self-service automation; reduced  |
|                       | reliance on Central IT for minor             |
|                       | enhancements; increased employee             |
|                       | satisfaction through skill acquisition.      |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &             | **Risk:** **Adoption Inertia.** Staff may    |
| Assumptions**         | deprioritize new tools due to existing       |
|                       | workload pressures.                          |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Mitigation:** Emphasize immediate          |
|                       | productivity benefits (\"Time Returned\")    |
|                       | rather than theoretical application.         |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Assumption:** Necessary licenses (Copilot, |
|                       | Cursor) are procured and provisioned prior   |
|                       | to launch.                                   |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+

## PROJECT 2: PMO PROCESS MANAGEMENT SYSTEM 

+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Field**             | **Details**                                  |
+=======================+==============================================+
| **Project Lead**      | Azmain Hossain (Product Owner) / Ben Brooks  |
|                       | (Technical Sponsor)                          |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic Context** | This system serves as the program\'s         |
|                       | \"Central Nervous System.\" It resolves the  |
|                       | historical ambiguity between \"Migration\"   |
|                       | (platform transition) and \"Adoption\"       |
|                       | (usage depth) by utilizing distinct data     |
|                       | models. It replaces passive reporting with   |
|                       | an active system that enforces operational   |
|                       | discipline and data governance.              |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**             | \- **Unified Dashboard:** A centralized view |
|                       | providing a definitive assessment of client  |
|                       | health, distinguishing between Migration     |
|                       | status and Adoption depth.                   |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Pipeline Management:** Tools to         |
|                       | automate weekly stand-ups, transforming them |
|                       | from status-gathering exercises into         |
|                       | strategic pipeline reviews of \"Blockers.\"  |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Data Hygiene (\"Compliance              |
|                       | Dashboard\"):** Features that visualize data |
|                       | gaps (e.g., missing \"Next Action\" fields)  |
|                       | and prompt users for remediation, ensuring   |
|                       | downstream reporting accuracy.               |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Executive View:** High-level            |
|                       | aggregation enabling leadership to assess    |
|                       | business health efficiently.                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Target Metrics**    | **Data Completeness %** (Minimizing          |
|                       | undefined status fields); **Stand-up         |
|                       | Efficiency** (Reducing status gathering time |
|                       | by \>50%).                                   |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits &          | **Customer:** CS Leadership & CSMs.          |
| Customers**           |                                              |
|                       | **Benefit:** Real-time visibility into       |
|                       | business health; standardized data           |
|                       | definitions eliminating reconciliation       |
|                       | debates; ability to manage by exception.     |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &             | **Risk:** **Integration Latency.**           |
| Assumptions**         | Infrastructure challenges with Azure Private |
|                       | Endpoints may delay the connection between   |
|                       | the Web App and Database.                    |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Mitigation:** Program Lead will act as     |
|                       | Release Manager, interfacing directly with   |
|                       | IT to resolve infrastructure tickets and     |
|                       | shield the development team.                 |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Assumption:** The proposed \"Migration\"   |
|                       | vs \"Adoption\" logic is applicable to \>90% |
|                       | of client scenarios.                         |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+

