## PROJECT 3: CUSTOMER SUCCESS AGENT (INTERIM DB → GAINSIGHT)

+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Field**   | **Details**                                            |
+=============+========================================================+
| **Project   | Kevin Purn / Richard Dosoo                             |
| Lead**      |                                                        |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic | To alleviate administrative burden on CSMs, this       |
| Context**   | project deploys autonomous agents for data entry and   |
|             | content creation. The strategy prioritizes             |
|             | **velocity** by utilizing an interim database for      |
|             | immediate value realization, while planning for a      |
|             | scalable enterprise architecture.                      |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**   | \- **Phase 1 (Velocity):** Immediate deployment of an  |
|             | \"Interim Database\" solution. This enables agents to  |
|             | summarize calls, draft emails, and update status       |
|             | fields immediately, validating use cases.              |
|             |                                                        |
|             | \- **Phase 2 (Scalability):** Migration of the backend |
|             | to the official Salesforce/Gainsight infrastructure    |
|             | once the data model is proven and APIs are available.  |
|             |                                                        |
|             | \- **Functionality:** Auto-summarization of calls,     |
|             | automated follow-up email drafting, action item        |
|             | extraction.                                            |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Target    | **Hours Saved per CSM/Week** (Measured via usage);     |
| Metrics**   | **Agent Utilization Rate** (Daily Active Agents).      |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits  | **Customer:** Individual CSMs.                         |
| &           |                                                        |
| Customers** | **Benefit:** Reduction of administrative overhead;     |
|             | increased capacity for high-value client interaction;  |
|             | consistent documentation quality across the team.      |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &   | **Risk:** **Technical Debt.** The potential for the    |
| As          | \"Interim Database\" to become a permanent legacy      |
| sumptions** | system if migration is delayed.                        |
|             |                                                        |
|             | **Mitigation:** Strict dual-track planning documented  |
|             | in the roadmap with a defined \"Sunset Date\" for the  |
|             | interim solution.                                      |
|             |                                                        |
|             | **Constraint:** The interim solution must adhere to    |
|             | existing Salesforce data hygiene standards.            |
+-------------+--------------------------------------------------------+

## PROJECT 4: ADOPTION CHARTER WORKFLOW (ENTRY POINT)

+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Field**             | **Details**                                  |
+=======================+==============================================+
| **Project Lead**      | Richard Dosoo / Liz Couchman                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic Context** | Standardizing the \"Input\" layer is         |
|                       | critical for the success of downstream AI    |
|                       | agents. This project digitizes the           |
|                       | onboarding process to ensure every customer  |
|                       | journey begins with structured, high-quality |
|                       | data, mitigating \"Garbage In, Garbage Out\" |
|                       | risks.                                       |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**             | \- **Digital Charters:** Conversion of       |
|                       | unstructured Word documents into dynamic     |
|                       | digital data models queryable by AI.         |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Auto-Documentation:** Utilization of    |
|                       | Copilot Studio to generate draft charters    |
|                       | from standard templates and Salesforce       |
|                       | records via CSM interview.                   |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Blueprint Integration:** Linking        |
|                       | customers to standard \"Blueprints\" (e.g.,  |
|                       | Treaty Pricing) to ensure standardized scope |
|                       | definitions.                                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Target Metrics**    | **Onboarding Time Reduction** (Time from     |
|                       | Sales to First Value); **Charter Data        |
|                       | Accuracy** (% of fields populating correctly |
|                       | downstream).                                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits &          | **Customer:** New Clients & Implementation   |
| Customers**           | Team.                                        |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Benefit:** Accelerated time-to-value;      |
|                       | high-quality data ingestion for AI           |
|                       | consumption; reduced administrative burden   |
|                       | during onboarding.                           |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &             | **Risk:** **Process Adherence.** CSMs may    |
| Assumptions**         | bypass the digital charter for complex       |
|                       | clients.                                     |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Mitigation:** Mandating the digital        |
|                       | charter as the requisite mechanism to unlock |
|                       | downstream resources (e.g., Implementation   |
|                       | Engineers).                                  |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+

## PROJECT 5: IRP NAVIGATOR UPGRADE (L1 AUTOMATION)

+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Field**             | **Details**                                  |
+=======================+==============================================+
| **Project Lead**      | Richard Dosoo / Matt Allen / Navigator       |
|                       | Product Team                                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic Context** | To decouple support volume from customer     |
|                       | growth, we must deflect Tier 1 support       |
|                       | tickets through self-service AI. This        |
|                       | project validates the technical feasibility  |
|                       | of utilizing the IRP Navigator as a          |
|                       | programmatic support agent.                  |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**             | \- **API Validation:** Rigorous testing of   |
|                       | Navigator APIs to ensure support for         |
|                       | programmatic access and high-volume          |
|                       | querying.                                    |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **L1 \"Salesforce Skill\":** Development  |
|                       | of a specialized agent \"skill\" to          |
|                       | intercept incoming tickets, reason against   |
|                       | the knowledge base, and propose immediate    |
|                       | solutions.                                   |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Target Metrics**    | **Ticket Deflection %** (Percentage of       |
|                       | potential L1 queries resolved without human  |
|                       | intervention); **Diagnostic Accuracy**.      |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits &          | **Customer:** End Users (Clients) & Internal |
| Customers**           | Support Desk.                                |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Benefit:** Immediate query resolution for  |
|                       | clients; reduced ticket volume for the       |
|                       | support team.                                |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &             | **Risk:** **Response Accuracy.** Potential   |
| Assumptions**         | for AI to provide incorrect technical        |
|                       | guidance (\"Hallucinations\").               |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Constraint:** Security approvals required  |
|                       | for accessing client-specific data.          |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Dependency:** Stability and rate limits of |
|                       | the Navigator API.                           |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+

## PROJECT 6: CURSOR FOR PIPELINE (SALES TOOL)

+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Field**             | **Details**                                  |
+=======================+==============================================+
| **Project Lead**      | Ben Brooks / Martin Davies / Pre-Sales       |
|                       | Engineering                                  |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Strategic Context** | This project reframes Cursor from an         |
|                       | internal efficiency tool to a revenue        |
|                       | generation engine. By constructing live      |
|                       | prototypes during client engagements, we     |
|                       | demonstrate the openness and flexibility of  |
|                       | our platform, countering \"black box\"       |
|                       | competitor narratives.                       |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Scope**             | \- **Pre-Sales Demos:** Enablement of        |
|                       | Solutions Engineers (SEs) to execute live    |
|                       | prototyping sessions (\"Build in 5           |
|                       | minutes\"), demonstrating rapid value        |
|                       | creation.                                    |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | \- **Rapid Prototyping:** Utilization of     |
|                       | Cursor to mock up complex integrations       |
|                       | during sales cycles to prove technical       |
|                       | feasibility.                                 |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Target Metrics**    | **Pipeline Conversion Lift** (Win rate for   |
|                       | deals utilizing Cursor demos vs. standard    |
|                       | demos); **Demo Velocity** (Time required to  |
|                       | prep a custom demo).                         |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Benefits &          | **Customer:** Sales Team & Prospective       |
| Customers**           | Clients.                                     |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Benefit:** Increased win rates; shortened  |
|                       | sales cycles; market differentiation via     |
|                       | \"Open Platform\" demonstration.             |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| **Risks &             | **Risk:** **Technical Proficiency.** Sales   |
| Assumptions**         | teams may lack confidence in live coding     |
|                       | environments.                                |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Mitigation:** Initial deployment of        |
|                       | dedicated \"Demo Engineering\" support to    |
|                       | shadow calls, transitioning to SE autonomy.  |
|                       |                                              |
|                       | **Dependency:** Availability of Cursor       |
|                       | licenses and curated \"sandbox\" datasets.   |
+-----------------------+----------------------------------------------+

